# Inventory — Configurable Rig Templates via Guild Config

## Files Directly Affected

### Will be modified

- `packages/plugins/spider/src/spider.ts` — Core change site. `buildStaticEngines()` will be replaced or wrapped by template-aware logic. `trySpawn()` calls `buildStaticEngines()` — will call template resolution instead. CDC handler in `start()` hardcodes `e.id === 'seal'` lookup — needs fallback. `start()` will call template validation on `spiderConfig`.
- `packages/plugins/spider/src/types.ts` — `SpiderConfig` gains `rigTemplates` field. New types needed: `RigTemplateEntry` (per-engine spec in a template), `RigTemplate` (ordered list), `RigTemplateMap` (keyed by writ type). GuildConfig module augmentation block already here and picks up the `SpiderConfig` change automatically.

### Will likely be created

- `packages/plugins/spider/src/template-validator.ts` (or inline in spider.ts) — pure validation function for templates; checks designId registry, upstream references, acyclicity.
- `packages/plugins/spider/src/resolve-givens.ts` (or inline) — variable interpolation logic; resolves `$writ`, `$role`, and `$spider.*` references.

### Will NOT be modified (confirmed unaffected)

- `packages/plugins/spider/src/engines/*.ts` — all five engine implementations are unchanged; they consume `givensSpec` as before.
- `packages/plugins/spider/src/tools/*.ts` — all tools unchanged.
- `packages/plugins/spider/src/index.ts` — re-exports unchanged; `SpiderConfig` is already re-exported.
- `packages/plugins/fabricator/src/fabricator.ts` — no changes to Fabricator itself; Spider calls it for design lookup during validation.
- `packages/plugins/clerk/src/types.ts` — `WritDoc.type` already exists; no changes.
- `packages/framework/core/src/guild-config.ts` — GuildConfig is open via module augmentation; no framework-level changes.

---

## Current Type Signatures (verbatim from source)

